# Cursor Rules for libsync

## Workspace Commands
- Always use `pnpm -F <workspace>` to run workspace-specific scripts
- Use `pnpm` for root-level scripts that use turbo
- Example: `pnpm -F libsync build` instead of `cd packages/cli && pnpm build`

## Package Management
- This is a pnpm workspace with turbo for task orchestration
- Main packages:
  - `libsync` (CLI package)
  - `@libsync/eslint-config` (ESLint configuration)
  - `@libsync/prettier-config` (Prettier configuration)

## Development Workflow
- Use turbo commands from root: `pnpm build`, `pnpm lint`, `pnpm typecheck`, `pnpm format`
- For individual package development, use `pnpm -F <package-name> <script>`
- Build outputs go to `cjs/` and `esm/` directories

## Code Standards
- TypeScript with strict mode enabled
- ESLint with custom configuration
- Prettier for formatting
- Node.js >= 20.16.0 required

